│ The issue seems to be related to the PHINode `%use` in the `exit` block, which is not   │
│ updated correctly during the vectorization process. Specifically, the PHINode `%use`    │
│ does not have the correct number of incoming values corresponding to its predecessors.  │
│ This is likely due to the `processLoop` function not properly handling the PHINodes in  │
│ the `exit` block after modifying the loop structure.                                    │
│                                                                                         │
│ To address this, we need to ensure that all PHINodes in the `exit` block are updated to │
│ match the new loop structure after vectorization. This involves verifying and fixing    │
│ the incoming values for each PHINode in the `exit` block.                               │
│                                                                                         │
│ I will now propose a fix for this issue.                                                │
